14/06/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- An IMF mission arrives in Bucharest on Tuesday (14 June) for negotiations with the government on continuation of the Fund's programme for the country.
The mission, headed by Emmanuel van der Mensbrugghe, will discuss economic performance and implementation of set budget targets in the first five months of this year, the macroeconomic situation, as well as the privatisation process.
In other news, a Bucharest court reaffirmed the legality Monday of the 20-day strike launched by the mechanics' union in the railway sector on 8 June.
The ruling came at the request of the National Company for Freight Railway Transport.
The protesters' main demand is for a 10 per cent wage increase.
(Rompres, Nine o'clock - 14/06/05)
